/-!
# Minor-arc exponential-sum bound

The geometric foundation of the circle method's **minor arcs** (the input, alongside
Vaughan's identity, to the Vinogradov bound on `вИС ќЫ(n) e(nќ±)` that drives almost-all
binary Goldbach вАФ see `AlmostAllGoldbachReduction.lean`).

Main results:
  вАҐ `MinorArc.exp_sum_bound` вАФ `вАЦвИС_{n<N} e(nќ±)вАЦ вЙ§ 1 / (2 ¬Ј dist(ќ±, вД§))`  for `ќ± вИЙ вД§`,
    where `e(x) = exp(2ѕАi x)` and `dist(ќ±, вД§) = |ќ± - round ќ±|`.
  вАҐ `MinorArc.char_orthogonality` вАФ `вИС_{n<q} e(an/q) = q¬Ј[qвИ£a]`, additive-character
    orthogonality (backbone of Gauss/Ramanujan sums + the major-arc singular series).
  вАҐ `MinorArc.integral_e` вАФ `вИЂвВА¬є e(kќ±) dќ± = [k=0]`, integral character orthogonality
    (circle-method main-term extractor; seed of the Parseval вЖТ large-sieve chain).
  вАҐ `MinorArc.parseval` вАФ `вИЂвВА¬є вАЦвИС_{n<N} aвВЩ e(nќ±)вАЦ¬≤ dќ± = вИС_{n<N} вАЦaвВЩвАЦ¬≤`, the L¬≤ mean
    value of an exponential sum (the circle-method variance engine; large-sieve base case).

Proof route (all elementary, Mathlib-only):
  вАҐ `geom_exp_bound`   вАФ for unit `z вЙ† 1`, `вАЦвИС_{n<N} zвБњвАЦ вЙ§ 2/вАЦz-1вАЦ`  (geometric sum + triangle).
  вАҐ `e_sub_one_norm`   вАФ `вАЦe(ќ±)-1вАЦ = 2|sin(ѕАќ±)|`  (chord length, via `normSq` + double angle).
  вАҐ `exp_sum_le_sin`   вАФ combine the two: `вАЦвИС e(nќ±)вАЦ вЙ§ 1/|sin(ѕАќ±)|`.
  вАҐ `two_dist_le_abs_sin` вАФ Jordan's inequality `2¬Јdist(ќ±,вД§) вЙ§ |sin(ѕАќ±)|`
                            (`Real.le_sin_mul` + `sin_add_int_mul_pi` periodicity).
  вАҐ `exp_sum_bound`    вАФ chain them to the `dist` form.

`#print axioms MinorArc.exp_sum_bound` = `[propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound]` вАФ axiom-free.
