/-! # Major-arc main term: `hmain` for almost-all Goldbach (Phase E)

This file builds the **main-term lower bound** the X-indexed weighted reduction consumes:

  `вИГ cвВА > 0, вИГ XвВА, вИА X вЙ• XвВА, вИА n even, X/2 < n вЙ§ X вЖТ cвВА¬ЈX вЙ§ Re (coeffModel (X+1) P Q n)`

with `P = вМК(log(X+1))^9вМЛвВК`, `Q = (X+1)/P`. Here `coeffModel` (defined in `RatedWindow.lean`)
is the truncated HardyвАУLittlewood model whose вДУ¬≤-closeness to the true Goldbach count
`repWeight` is `core_variance` (Phase D). Fed to
`GoldbachReduction.almost_all_goldbach_of_weighted_variance_indexed` with `m X n := Re (вА¶)`,
`ќі X := cвВА¬ЈX`, this discharges `hmain`; `hnegl` is an elementary log-vs-вИЪ tail.

## Route (Re coeffModel = рЭФЦ_P(n)¬Јr_N(n) + error)

Writing `W(q,a) = вИС_r e(ra/q)¬ЈlambdaModel q r = ќЉ(q)/ѕЖ(q)` (BANKED: `lambdaModel_coeff`,
`ramanujan_sum_coprime` in `MinorArcExpSum.lean`), the model is
